The Duke And I|Julia Quinn|Avon|The first book in the Bridgerton series. Daphne Bridgerton’s reputation soars when she colludes with the Duke of Hastings. The basis of the Netflix series “Bridgerton.”
Shadows In Death|JD Robb|St. Martin's|The 51st book of the In Death series. A hitman with possible connections to Eve Dallas’s husband is seen near the scene of a crime.
The Inn|James Patterson with Candice Fox|Grand Central|A former Boston police detective who is now an innkeeper must shield a seaside town from a crew of criminals.
An Irish Wish|Nora Roberts|Silhouette|Two romance stories: “Irish Rose” and “Irish Rebel.”
The Lost And Found Bookshop|Susan Wiggs|Avon|Natalie Harper takes over the care of her mother’s bookshop and her ailing grandfather.
A Minute To Midnight|David Baldacci|Grand Central|When Atlee Pine returns to her hometown to investigate her sister’s kidnapping from 30 years ago, she winds up tracking a potential serial killer.
Moral Compass|Danielle Steel|Dell|Shortly after Saint Ambrose Prep goes co-ed, a student is attacked and the community falls apart.
Finally You|Debbie Macomber|MIRA|Two romance stories: “No Competition” and “All Things Considered.”
Preacher'S Carnage|William W Johnstone,JA Johnstone|Pinnacle|Preacher is hired by a St. Louis businessman to seek justice for an ambushed wagon train on the Sante Fe trail.
Bitter Pill|Fern Michaels|Zebra/Kensington|The 32nd book in the Sisterhood series. Doctors in different parts of the world push questionable natural remedies.
Unsolved|James Patterson,David Ellis|Grand Central|A string of seemingly accidental and unrelated deaths confound F.B.I. agent Emmy Dockery.
The Viscount Who Loved Me|Julia Quinn|Avon|The second book in the Bridgerton series. Kate Sheffield gets in the way of Anthony Bridgerton's intent to marry.
Blood In The Dust|William W Johnstone,JA Johnstone|Pinnacle|The second book in the Hunter Buchanon Black Hills Western series. A former tracker goes back into action when a saloon girl gets kidnapped.
The Warsaw Protocol|Steve Berry|St. Martin's|The 15th book in the Cotton Malone series. The balance of power in Europe is imperiled.
Sisters By Choice|Susan Mallery|MIRA|The fourth book in the Blackberry Island series. Three women seek to make changes in their lives that they find difficult.
